{"word":"Gaza","slug":"gaza","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Gaza</b> <a href=\"#/H5804\">H5804</a><br/><a href=\"#/G1048\">G1048</a> <br/> 1. Called also Azzah<br/> - A city of the Philistines<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=13&verse=3'>Jos 13:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=25&verse=20'>Jer 25:20</a> <br/> - One of the border cities of the Canaanites<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=10&verse=19'>Gen 10:19</a> <br/> - A city of the Avim and Anakim<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=2&verse=23'>Deu 2:23</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=11&verse=22'>Jos 11:22</a> <br/> - Allotted to Judah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=15&verse=47'>Jos 15:47</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=1&verse=18'>Jdg 1:18</a> <br/> - A temple of Dagon, situated at<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=16&verse=23'>Jdg 16:23</a> <br/> - Samson dies at<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=16&verse=31'>Jdg 16:31</a> <br/> - On the western boundary of the kingdom of Israel in the time of Solomon<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=4&verse=24'>1Ki 4:24</a> <br/> - Smitten by Pharaoh<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=47&verse=1'>Jer 47:1</a> <br/> - Prophecies relating to<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=30&chapter=1&verse=7'>Amo 1:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=36&chapter=2&verse=4'>Zep 2:4</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=38&chapter=9&verse=5'>Zec 9:5</a> <br/> - Desert of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=8&verse=39'>Act 8:39</a> <br/> 2. A city of Ephraim<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=6&verse=4'>Jdg 6:4</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=7&verse=28'>1Ch 7:28</a>"}]}